{
  "stem": "6719.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he rips it off and gives it to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he said-- and he puts his hand in his pockets and he says, and here's 20 francs so that you can take the streetcar.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I said, who are you?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He said, I'm with the whoever the Jewish organization was that took care of people that returned.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That's the number one thing, because you-- you asked me how I feel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "When we arrived in Canada on the first of February, 1951, we sat on the Union Station because we had to wait for a train.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We could have taken a streetcar, but we didn't know any better.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we waited, and a guy walks up to me and he says to me, he says, you just arrive here?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "You Jewish?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is in English.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now I said yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I didn't get mad to hit him because I could see that he was Jewish too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, look, I'm from the Jewish Congress Beverly Street, bah bah bah bah bah.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you ever need anything right there-- if you need a loan or something like that, or you need some food, like that-- takes it off, gives it to me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can you tell me what other people in the world act like that?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You tell me and I'll tell you that it isn't so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's-- it's-- it's-- this is the greatest feeling in the world.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It didn't make me religious, but it made me one thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm-- I'm-- I'm as nationalistic about who I am and what I am, and I want to instill this in my daughter and in my granddaughter.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, uh--",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
